@@eThe Forest of Confusion: Western Containment Assessment@@N

@@yBureau of Western Routes, Interinstitutional Liability Division@@N
@@dFiled under: Kiess Jurisdiction, Conclave Connection, Containment@@N

The Forest of Confusion is, in jurisdictional terms, @@yKiess's
problem@@N. It lies north of their walls. Their waystones mark its
southern margin. When the mist contracts their reliable perimeter each
season, it is their wardens who lose ground. Our Bureau notes this
with professional sympathy and careful distance.

But the @@WSpirebound Conclave@@N connection makes distance impossible.

The confusion mists were a deliberately engineered quarantine created
by druids to contain @@lcrystal matrices@@N the Conclave embedded in the
forest's root systems. The Conclave -- the same institution our
ledgers record receiving @@d"forty iron bars and six condemned
debtors"@@N from Midgaard's requisition offices. We @@yfunded the
Conclave@@N. Our iron built their resonance anchors. Our citizens
became their test subjects. When the Conclave collapsed, they left
crystal contamination someone else had to contain.

The druids who maintained the quarantine did competent work. Calibrated
mist boundaries, selective path-rerouting, chemical disorientation
tuned to discourage without killing -- @@yinstitutional maintenance@@N
of a high order, performed without ledgers or oaths. It is humbling,
and our clerks do not enjoy being humbled.

Then the druidic order died. Not dramatically, but @@ddemographically@@N.
Without maintenance, the mists diffused outward. The quarantine became
the hazard. Bureau assessment: @@rcontainment failure through
institutional succession collapse@@N.

Three systems now collide. @@yKiess civic order@@N pushes south, losing
ground each season. The @@gVerdant ecological intelligence@@N produces
chemical disorientation protecting the deep interior. @@dWithered
Conclave residue@@N weaponizes disorientation into attritional hazard.
@@gTreants@@N guard as sentinels. @@rNeogi@@N slavers exploit the fog.
@@dBroken ones@@N congregate where the quarantine once held.

Our Bureau maintains a @@dliability register@@N tracking Midgaard's
indirect responsibility: iron shipments, debtor transfers, enabling
decisions that produced the contamination the druids spent
generations containing.

The Continuity faction insists our Conclave transactions were wartime
pragmatism. The Reckoning faction insists they were @@rthe first link
in a chain that ends in a forest full of broken people and
uncalibrated poison@@N. The Forest is Kiess's to manage. But @@rthe
reason it exists is partly ours@@N.
